Webshot uses CasperJS, and any interaction code would likely be built on CasperJS. CasperJS is a library specifically for PhantomJS, which in turn is no longer being developed.

As @jimhester mentioned, the [webdriver](https://github.com/rstudio/webdriver) package is a better way to do interaction. (The reason that webshot doesn't use webdriver is that webdriver has several dependencies, and there are some applications where webshot is used it's important to have few dependencies.)

